Program: The History Hour
Title: When France Said 'Non' to Britain Joining Europe
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csvsv5
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 14 Jan 2018
When France stopped Britain joining Europe in the 1960s, the boy who set a record for continuously staying awake, the launch of the first iPhone, hands reaching out in friendship between Britain and Germany after the Second World War, and a notorious massacre during Algeria's bitter internal conflict of the 1990s. Photo: Charles de Gaulle, President of France, at a press conference on 14th January 1963 at which he said Britain was not ready to join the European Economic Community, now the EU (Credit: Central Press/Getty Images) Show less